From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0014/N] copy_bsd_aarch64: CHERI fallback for COPY_SMALL macro

`COPY_SMALL` is a hand-rolled small-copy inline-asm fast path using
non-cap A64 `ldr`/`str`/`ldp`/`stp` with `[%[s], #0]` operands. Under
CHERI/Morello purecap, the assembler rejects capability-typed
operands for those mnemonics and emits
`error: invalid operand for instruction`.

For Phase 1 ("make it build") we substitute a `memcpy`-based fallback
when `__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__` is defined. A cap-aware fast path
using `LDR Cx`/`STP Cx` is Phase 2 work — it requires deciding
whether the GC's small-copy primitive needs to preserve capability
tags (yes, for oop arrays).

NB: copy_bsd_aarch64.hpp is `#include CPU_HEADER(copy)`-d *inside*
the body of `class Copy`. We must not introduce top-level
`#include`s here — they would land inside the class scope and break
the parse with "missing '}' at end of definition of 'Copy'". The
existing `memcpy` calls in `pd_disjoint_words` etc. show that
`memcpy` is already in scope via the parent translation unit, so the
fallback can use unqualified `memcpy`.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0014)

--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/copy_bsd_aarch64.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/copy_bsd_aarch64.hpp
@@ -27,6 +27,15 @@
 #ifndef OS_CPU_BSD_AARCH64_COPY_BSD_AARCH64_HPP
 #define OS_CPU_BSD_AARCH64_COPY_BSD_AARCH64_HPP

+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI/Morello purecap: the inline-asm fast path below uses non-cap
+// ldr/str/ldp/stp operand forms that the purecap assembler rejects as
+// invalid. Fall back to memcpy for the small-copy path; a cap-aware
+// fast path is Phase 2 work.
+#define COPY_SMALL(from, to, count) \
+  memcpy(static_cast<void*>(to), static_cast<const void*>(from), \
+         (count) * sizeof(HeapWord))
+#else
 #define COPY_SMALL(from, to, count)                                     \
 {                                                                       \
         long tmp0, tmp1, tmp2, tmp3;                                    \
@@ -99,6 +108,7 @@
   :                                                                     \
   : "memory", "cc");                                                    \
 }
+#endif // __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__

 static void pd_conjoint_words(const HeapWord* from, HeapWord* to, size_t count) {
   __asm volatile( "prfm pldl1strm, [%[s], #0];" :: [s]"r"(from) : "memory");
